WEBVTT

00:02.210 --> 00:04.420
Do you know
Chloe Brown Mueller

00:04.420 --> 00:07.170
is running for
Fairfield County councilperson?

00:07.170 --> 00:10.210
I've been trying to think of
a way to deface her lawn signs

00:10.210 --> 00:12.040
by rearranging the letters
in her name.

00:12.040 --> 00:13.880
Cross out the "C"
and the "H",

00:13.880 --> 00:15.290
slip in an "S",
add an "R".

00:15.290 --> 00:16.290
It spells "Loser".

00:16.290 --> 00:18.040
Ah. Sounds like
a lot of work.

00:18.040 --> 00:19.710
I think I'll just draw
penises on them.

00:19.710 --> 00:22.420
[ Hans Gruber oinking ]

00:22.420 --> 00:23.920
Anna-Kat, how many times
have I told you?

00:23.920 --> 00:26.290
Do not feed Hans Gruber
from the table.

00:26.290 --> 00:28.540
He's only gaining
10 pounds a day.

00:28.540 --> 00:30.210
He's wasting away
to nothing!

00:30.210 --> 00:32.080
Hans, go!

00:32.080 --> 00:34.170
[ Sighs ]

00:34.170 --> 00:36.750
Oliver,
dinner table -- now.

00:36.750 --> 00:39.040
I'm waiting for
my Mandarin grade to post.

00:39.040 --> 00:40.920
Why are you so worked up
about this grade?

00:40.920 --> 00:42.290
You always get
straight A's.

00:42.290 --> 00:44.330
I know I do,
but Jeremy Fleisher's

00:44.330 --> 00:46.670
gonna obliterate the curve
in my Mandarin class.

00:46.670 --> 00:48.290
How do you know that?

00:48.290 --> 00:50.920
His parents just brought
him a 12-year-old from
China for Christmas.

00:50.920 --> 00:54.080
His parents brought him
a 12-year-old human being?

00:54.080 --> 00:56.210
No, it's a foreign
exchange program.

00:56.210 --> 00:57.710
They're supposed to
teach the kid English,

00:57.710 --> 01:00.080
but instead, they make him
tutor Jeremy in Mandarin.

01:02.040 --> 01:04.080
Could I please
have more --
Unh-unh-unh!
You know the rules.

01:09.580 --> 01:11.920
[ Both chuckle ]

01:13.580 --> 01:14.620
Grades are in.

01:14.620 --> 01:18.710
♪♪

01:18.710 --> 01:20.460
I got a B-plus?!

01:20.460 --> 01:22.040
My life is ruined!

01:22.040 --> 01:23.040
Ruined!

01:23.040 --> 01:24.460
A B-plus is great.

01:24.460 --> 01:25.790
Of course you think
a B-plus is great --

01:25.790 --> 01:27.420
'cause your life
is a C-minus!

01:27.420 --> 01:28.710
Hey!

01:28.710 --> 01:30.880
Calm...down!

01:30.880 --> 01:34.080
You're in eighth grade.
Eighth grade doesn't count.

01:34.080 --> 01:37.040
It all counts!
It all counts!

01:37.040 --> 01:39.460
He's really worked up.
He's doing that thing
where he repeats everything.

01:39.460 --> 01:40.960
Honey, let me give you
some perspective.

01:40.960 --> 01:42.250
Take your father and me.

01:42.250 --> 01:44.670
He was obsessed
with grades.

01:44.670 --> 01:48.420
Me -- I didn't worry so much
and just enjoyed my life.

01:48.420 --> 01:49.670
Guess what.

01:49.670 --> 01:51.620
We wound up
in the same place --

01:51.620 --> 01:53.290
same house.

01:53.290 --> 01:54.460
Actually, I'm doing
a little better

01:54.460 --> 01:56.620
because I don't
have to go to work.

01:56.620 --> 01:59.120
And you don't have to wear
real pants if you don't want to.

01:59.120 --> 02:01.670
And I don't have to wear
real pants if I don't want to!

02:01.670 --> 02:03.620
I'm on a track,
and it starts here.

02:03.620 --> 02:05.380
I have to become
valedictorian,

02:05.380 --> 02:08.420
then it goes Harvard,
Wharton, Goldman Sachs,

02:08.420 --> 02:09.750
then a remodel
in the Hamptons

02:09.750 --> 02:11.880
that my second wife
can busy herself with.

02:11.880 --> 02:13.920
I'm probably gonna like
your first wife.

02:13.920 --> 02:16.080
Don't be mad when I maintain
a relationship with her.

02:18.830 --> 02:20.420
He puts way too much pressure
on himself.

02:20.420 --> 02:22.250
I know. This is
getting out of hand.

02:22.250 --> 02:23.750
Do you think he should
talk to somebody?

02:23.750 --> 02:25.120
He's not listening
to us.

02:25.120 --> 02:26.420
Someone to give him
a little perspective.

02:26.420 --> 02:27.750
Yeah.

02:27.750 --> 02:29.790
And I think
I know just the person.

02:29.790 --> 02:32.330
I don't even know
why I'm here.

02:32.330 --> 02:34.500
You're here
because you need my help.

02:34.500 --> 02:36.670
You need to learn how
to take your mind off of school.

02:36.670 --> 02:38.500
I saw this YouTube video
about this girl

02:38.500 --> 02:40.330
who was really driven,
like you,

02:40.330 --> 02:43.080
and she eventually cracked up
and got Auto-Tuned into a song.

02:43.080 --> 02:44.330
The song is really funny

02:44.330 --> 02:46.380
if you forget
that she's dead inside.

02:46.380 --> 02:48.170
Okay, dumb Yoda,

02:48.170 --> 02:49.830
what advice
do you have for me?

02:49.830 --> 02:52.710
Start binge-watching something.
It'll help turn your brain off.

02:52.710 --> 02:54.920
Easier for you,
'cause yours was never on.

02:54.920 --> 02:56.580
You should listen to me.

02:56.580 --> 02:59.210
Watch a dozen seasons
of "Grey's Anatomy" in a row.

02:59.210 --> 03:01.210
You're not gonna care
if you get into Harvard or not

03:01.210 --> 03:04.120
once you've seen a bomb
get pulled out of a body
for the fourth time.

03:04.120 --> 03:06.000
Hey, I am
going to Harvard!

03:06.000 --> 03:07.750
I even practice
that phony evasive thing

03:07.750 --> 03:09.500
where I tell people
I go to college in Boston.

03:10.710 --> 03:12.290
"Oh. B.U.?"

03:12.290 --> 03:14.710
[ Chuckles ]
"No -- Harvard".

03:14.710 --> 03:18.500
♪♪

03:18.500 --> 03:20.170
Man on TV:
Ni ai wo ma.

03:21.710 --> 03:24.170
Ni ai wo ma.

03:24.170 --> 03:25.580
Ni ai wo ma.
Oliver: Ni ai wo ma.

03:25.580 --> 03:26.960
[ Remote clicks ]

03:26.960 --> 03:28.250
Ni ai wo ma.
Ni ai wo ma.

03:28.250 --> 03:29.330
[ Remote clicks ]

03:29.330 --> 03:30.460
[ Hans Gruber snorting ]

03:30.460 --> 03:31.880
Ni ai wo ma.
Ni ai wo ma.

03:31.880 --> 03:33.960
Oliver,
why aren't you in bed?

03:33.960 --> 03:35.540
I'm practicing
my Mandarin.

03:35.540 --> 03:37.710
I'm using Taylor's
stolen Netflix password

03:37.710 --> 03:39.330
to watch
a Chinese soap opera.

03:39.330 --> 03:42.330
It's 2:30 in the morning.
You need to get some sleep.

03:42.330 --> 03:44.830
You keep this up, you'll burn
out before high school ends

03:44.830 --> 03:46.380
and end up
at some safety school.

03:46.380 --> 03:47.830
I'm not going to Cornell!

03:47.830 --> 03:49.000
Come on!

03:49.000 --> 03:51.790
♪♪

03:51.790 --> 03:52.830
[ Sighs ]

03:52.830 --> 03:54.330
Bed.

03:54.330 --> 03:57.380
[ Speaking
broken Mandarin ]

03:57.380 --> 03:59.000
That sounded a little like
"Go [bleep] yourself".

04:03.620 --> 04:05.620
♪♪

04:05.620 --> 04:07.330
I'm worried
about Oliver.

04:07.330 --> 04:10.380
He's obsessed with his grades
and not enjoying his life.

04:10.380 --> 04:12.170
He wants to go
to SAT camp this summer.

04:12.170 --> 04:13.580
Can you believe
that's a thing?

04:13.580 --> 04:15.330
Oh, yeah --
I lied about my kids' ages

04:15.330 --> 04:16.960
so they could start
when they were 6.

04:16.960 --> 04:19.170
They have no fun activities --
just studying.

04:19.170 --> 04:21.080
Oh, and I checked the box
saying they could hit them.

04:21.080 --> 04:22.670
Ugh.
Remember
when we thought

04:22.670 --> 04:24.790
having that baby
would soften you up?

04:24.790 --> 04:26.830
[ Laughter ]

04:26.830 --> 04:28.670
We were so stupid.

04:28.670 --> 04:30.670
[ Laughter ]

04:30.670 --> 04:32.000
Hello, ladies!

04:32.000 --> 04:36.120
Be very still. Her vision
is based on movement.

04:36.120 --> 04:39.790
[ Laughs ]
You are so funny!

04:39.790 --> 04:42.330
Hey, would you mind
putting one of my campaign signs

04:42.330 --> 04:43.920
in your teeny,
tiny yard?

04:43.920 --> 04:46.750
Why would you want
your sign in my yard?

04:46.750 --> 04:48.710
All you ever do
is insult my house.

04:48.710 --> 04:50.830
That was just
playfully joking around!

04:50.830 --> 04:52.290
Right, Maria?

04:52.290 --> 04:54.750
Tell Katie I'm funny
and I like to joke around.

04:54.750 --> 04:56.040
You're funny.

04:56.040 --> 04:57.670
And I like
to joke around!

04:57.670 --> 04:58.920
She likes
to joke around.

04:58.920 --> 05:00.580
[ Sighing ] Okay.
Seriously, Maria?

05:00.580 --> 05:03.250
I pay you $7.45 an hour,
plus Obamacare

05:03.250 --> 05:04.540
to be more convincing
than that.

05:04.540 --> 05:06.120
[ Sighs ]

05:06.120 --> 05:07.830
Okay, truth time --

05:07.830 --> 05:10.170
Fairfield County is bigger
than just Westport,

05:10.170 --> 05:11.710
so if I'm gonna
win this thing,

05:11.710 --> 05:13.540
I need to appeal
to the poors.

05:13.540 --> 05:15.620
Ugh.
I'd put one
in Maria's yard,

05:15.620 --> 05:17.620
but she doesn't have one,
'cause she lives in a condo...

05:17.620 --> 05:19.500
[ Laughs ]
...with her parents!

05:19.500 --> 05:21.040
Ull! [ Laughs ]

05:21.040 --> 05:22.250
My mother
is very sick.

05:22.250 --> 05:24.000
Oh, sick of you!

05:24.000 --> 05:25.080
Up top.

05:25.080 --> 05:26.330
[ Rattling ]

05:26.330 --> 05:27.830
No, you missed it.
You missed it.

05:27.830 --> 05:29.710
I'm not putting
your stupid sign in my yard.

05:29.710 --> 05:32.250
And tell your husband to return
my husband's phone calls.

05:32.250 --> 05:33.830
Oh, well,
Stan's out of the country,

05:33.830 --> 05:35.290
so I will
pass the message along.

05:35.290 --> 05:36.330
[ Huffs ]

05:36.330 --> 05:37.670
Aah! So hot!

05:37.670 --> 05:39.750
Oh! Zip it, Maria! Okay?
You're making a scene!

05:39.750 --> 05:41.210
[ Exhales sharply ]

05:41.210 --> 05:42.210
[ Door opens ]
Go!

05:43.790 --> 05:44.830
Ugh.

05:44.830 --> 05:46.250
Nicely played --

05:46.250 --> 05:47.830
sticking it
to Chloe Brown Mueller

05:47.830 --> 05:49.080
with a Stan question.

05:49.080 --> 05:50.290
What are you
talking about?

05:50.290 --> 05:52.420
You haven't heard?
Stan took off.

05:52.420 --> 05:54.250
Yeah. He went to Nepal
to find himself.

05:54.250 --> 05:55.500
He's drinking
yak butter tea

05:55.500 --> 05:57.460
and deciding on
which god to pray to.

05:57.460 --> 06:00.210
He had a huge midlife crisis
and snapped.

06:00.210 --> 06:01.620
That's why
Chloe's running for office.

06:01.620 --> 06:02.880
She's putting on
a big show,

06:02.880 --> 06:04.670
pretending they're both
"doing their own thing".

06:04.670 --> 06:06.460
Oh, it's so sad...

06:06.460 --> 06:08.120
that I didn't know that.

06:08.120 --> 06:09.710
I would've
enjoyed it more.

06:09.710 --> 06:11.460
[ Laughs ]

06:11.460 --> 06:13.790
Stan's a perfect example
of someone who pushed himself,

06:13.790 --> 06:15.710
went to all the right schools,
got a high-powered job,

06:15.710 --> 06:18.290
then wakes up and realizes
he got everything he wanted

06:18.290 --> 06:19.830
but hated his whole life.

06:19.830 --> 06:23.210
Oh, my God.
Oliver is on that same path.

06:23.210 --> 06:25.000
How do I stop my son
from growing up

06:25.000 --> 06:27.290
and having
a midlife crisis?

06:27.290 --> 06:29.960
You get ahead of it.
Give him a midlife crisis now.

06:29.960 --> 06:31.500
Or...

06:31.500 --> 06:34.080
check this box, and I could
smack him around for you.

06:34.080 --> 06:35.580
Mnh-mnh.

06:35.580 --> 06:38.420
Come on.
[ Laughs ]

06:38.420 --> 06:39.420
Boom!

06:39.420 --> 06:41.040
[ Laughter ]

06:41.040 --> 06:44.290
♪♪

06:44.290 --> 06:46.580
Whatever it is,
I don't have time.

06:46.580 --> 06:47.710
I'm studying.

06:47.710 --> 06:49.620
Well, get it
out of your system now,

06:49.620 --> 06:52.880
because tomorrow we're moving up
your midlife crisis,

06:52.880 --> 06:54.750
and that begins
with ditching school.

06:54.750 --> 06:56.170
I can't ditch school!

06:56.170 --> 06:58.000
My science notebook review
is tomorrow and --

06:58.000 --> 06:59.460
Hey!
I'm your mother.

06:59.460 --> 07:01.330
And when I say,
"You're ditching school",

07:01.330 --> 07:02.670
you're ditching school.

07:02.670 --> 07:04.460
But if I get caught, it could
go on my permanent record.

07:04.460 --> 07:05.830
There's no such thing.

07:05.830 --> 07:07.880
Now, stop studying and watch
"Ferris Bueller's Day Off"

07:07.880 --> 07:09.040
tonight for inspiration.

07:09.040 --> 07:10.580
Can I watch it
in Mandarin?

07:10.580 --> 07:11.580
Nyet!

07:11.580 --> 07:12.580
That's Russian.

07:12.580 --> 07:14.000
Shut up, smarty-pants.

07:14.000 --> 07:18.250
♪♪

07:18.250 --> 07:20.830
I need an extra treat
to bring for Franklin.

07:20.830 --> 07:23.210
He'd never tasted sugar
before he met me.

07:23.210 --> 07:24.670
Do you think
maybe Franklin's parents

07:24.670 --> 07:25.830
don't want him
eating candy?

07:25.830 --> 07:27.170
Yeah, I get that.

07:27.170 --> 07:28.540
He gets all amped up,
and then it's all

07:28.540 --> 07:31.290
"Blah, blah, blah"
about his diabetes.

07:31.290 --> 07:33.750
New rule --
no feeding Franklin sugar.

07:33.750 --> 07:35.580
Hey, would either of you
be interested

07:35.580 --> 07:37.710
in going to a stamp unveiling
at the library?

07:37.710 --> 07:38.710
Not it!

07:38.710 --> 07:39.830
How about if I told you

07:39.830 --> 07:41.960
it's a rare banana stamp
that's a misprint?

07:41.960 --> 07:43.250
Turns out
it's a plantain.

07:43.250 --> 07:44.330
Not it!

07:44.330 --> 07:46.620
Don't you have a friend
you can go with?

07:46.620 --> 07:48.170
Not really --
not since Stan left.

07:48.170 --> 07:49.500
So find someone else.

07:49.500 --> 07:51.500
It's not easy making friends
once you get older.

07:51.500 --> 07:53.500
I tried this
Adult Friend Finder website.

07:53.500 --> 07:55.670
It was not
what I thought it was.

07:55.670 --> 07:57.040
I have an idea.

07:57.040 --> 07:58.750
Why don't you take Anna-Kat
to the park?

07:58.750 --> 08:00.290
There's always dads
hanging around.

08:00.290 --> 08:01.540
Maybe you can
meet someone there.

08:01.540 --> 08:02.790
I don't know.

08:02.790 --> 08:05.080
Hey, anyone would be lucky
to be your friend.

08:06.460 --> 08:07.380
Okay.

08:08.790 --> 08:10.080
Alright,
everybody in the car.

08:12.290 --> 08:14.460
Are you sure making Oliver
skip school is a good idea?

08:14.460 --> 08:16.750
Trust me --
it's just what he needed.

08:16.750 --> 08:18.120
He's even sleeping in.

08:18.120 --> 08:19.620
Not a bad start
to his ditch day.

08:19.620 --> 08:21.460
I don't remember
agreeing to this.

08:21.460 --> 08:23.580
This isn't one of those
things that we both
have to sign off on.

08:23.580 --> 08:25.380
Oh, so you get to do
whatever you want with Oliver,

08:25.380 --> 08:27.500
but I buy one rug from Cost Plus
without consult--

08:27.500 --> 08:30.250
Rugs are different
than kids, Greg!

08:30.250 --> 08:36.250
♪♪

08:37.250 --> 08:39.420
Oliver, I would not
be a good mother

08:39.420 --> 08:42.500
if I let you
sleep away your ditch day.

08:42.500 --> 08:44.380
[ Snoring ]

08:44.380 --> 08:46.170
[ Singsong voice ]
Oliver!

08:46.170 --> 08:47.620
[ Snoring continues ]

08:47.620 --> 08:51.210
♪♪

08:51.210 --> 08:53.750
What the...

08:53.750 --> 08:55.830
[ Hans Gruber oinks ]

08:55.830 --> 08:58.460
Katie: He went to school!
He reverse-Ferris Buellered me.

08:58.460 --> 09:00.880
And instead of a mannequin,
it's a pig!

09:00.880 --> 09:02.920
Oliver thinks he's pulled
a fast one on me.

09:02.920 --> 09:04.330
I'll show him.

09:04.330 --> 09:06.250
I'm not washing these sheets
for a month.

09:06.250 --> 09:08.080
[ Oinking continues ]

09:12.500 --> 09:14.170
[ Speaking Mandarin ]

09:16.210 --> 09:18.120
I need to speak with
Oliver Otto.

09:21.080 --> 09:22.420
Son, I want you to know

09:22.420 --> 09:23.960
I wake up every night
drenched in sweat

09:23.960 --> 09:26.830
because my job entails
delivering news like this.

09:26.830 --> 09:28.710
News like what?
What are you talking about?

09:28.710 --> 09:30.380
I sweat
right through my pajamas.

09:30.380 --> 09:33.040
Then I lay there alone,
shivering in the dark,

09:33.040 --> 09:34.380
staring into the abyss.

09:34.380 --> 09:36.710
But I've trained
for this moment.

09:36.710 --> 09:38.420
Your mother's
been in an accident.

09:38.420 --> 09:40.580
There's a car
waiting for you outside.

09:40.580 --> 09:46.580
♪♪

09:47.920 --> 09:49.580
[ Sighs ]

09:49.580 --> 09:50.880
Mom, what happened?

09:50.880 --> 09:52.500
Principal Ablin
said you had an accident.

09:52.500 --> 09:53.670
I did.

09:53.670 --> 09:56.420
I did have an accident.

09:56.420 --> 09:59.580
I opened up a bag of Bugles,
and they went...

09:59.580 --> 10:01.040
everywhere.

10:02.710 --> 10:04.500
[ Laughs ]

10:04.500 --> 10:06.460
You are a psychopath.

10:06.460 --> 10:08.960
Mother/son ditch day,
here we come!

10:08.960 --> 10:10.210
I'm going
back to school.

10:11.620 --> 10:12.420
[ Lock clicks ]

10:15.380 --> 10:18.620
What I really meant to say is,
I'm glad you're okay.

10:18.620 --> 10:19.750
Aw, sweetie.

10:22.670 --> 10:23.830
[ Button clicks twice ]

10:23.830 --> 10:25.330
Are you holding your finger
on the door lock

10:25.330 --> 10:26.710
while you hug me
with only one arm?

10:26.710 --> 10:28.120
I don't know.

10:28.120 --> 10:29.210
Are you trying
to unlock the door

10:29.210 --> 10:30.920
while you hug me
with only one arm?

10:30.920 --> 10:32.000
[ Button clicking ]

10:32.000 --> 10:34.330
♪♪

10:34.330 --> 10:35.920
[ Locks clicking rapidly ]

10:35.920 --> 10:41.920
♪♪

10:43.210 --> 10:45.040
That's it!
I'm driving while locking!

10:45.040 --> 10:46.620
I'm driving
while locking!

10:46.620 --> 10:48.620
[ Clicking continues ]

10:48.620 --> 10:54.620
♪♪

10:56.040 --> 10:57.380
There you go.

10:57.380 --> 10:59.540
Just get in the circle.

10:59.540 --> 11:00.750
Just edge your way in.

11:03.080 --> 11:04.500
That's it. That's it.

11:10.040 --> 11:11.460
That's not it.

11:11.460 --> 11:17.460
♪♪

11:17.460 --> 11:18.460
Giants fan, huh?

11:18.460 --> 11:20.000
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.710
They've got to figure out
their quarterback problem, huh?

11:21.710 --> 11:23.040
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah. Yeah.

11:25.080 --> 11:26.580
You like stamps?

11:28.750 --> 11:30.000
Oh, Greg.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.710
♪♪

11:31.710 --> 11:34.040
Hey, look! You two
have the same sneakers.

11:34.040 --> 11:35.670
Why don't you
talk about it?

11:35.670 --> 11:37.000
New Balance.

11:37.000 --> 11:39.120
Yeah -- the shoe
of dads everywhere.

11:39.120 --> 11:40.960
[ Chuckles ]
I'm Greg.

11:40.960 --> 11:42.000
Charles.
Oh, nice to meet you.

11:42.000 --> 11:43.380
Yeah, it's good
to meet you, too.

11:43.380 --> 11:46.170
So, Cassidy, is that your dad
my dad's talking to?

11:46.170 --> 11:47.920
Yup.

11:47.920 --> 11:49.540
They seem to be
getting along.

11:49.540 --> 11:50.710
Look.

11:50.710 --> 11:52.040
[ Both laugh ]

11:52.040 --> 11:53.250
So...cute.

11:55.670 --> 11:57.170
Do you want to come over
to my house

11:57.170 --> 11:58.620
for a playdate
later today?

11:58.620 --> 11:59.750
Okay.

12:02.460 --> 12:03.620
[ Laughs ]

12:03.620 --> 12:05.380
Oh, my God!

12:05.380 --> 12:08.000
Why is that funny?
You're filthy now.

12:08.000 --> 12:09.830
Sandy belly!
Ho ho ho!

12:09.830 --> 12:11.670
[ Giggling ]

12:13.540 --> 12:15.460
The things
I do for him.

12:15.460 --> 12:17.580
[ Laughing ]

12:17.580 --> 12:19.920
You can't tell me
this hasn't been a fun day.

12:19.920 --> 12:21.380
We snuck into a movie,

12:21.380 --> 12:23.000
half-made a Build-A-Bear,
then ran out,

12:23.000 --> 12:24.330
and went
engagement ring shopping

12:24.330 --> 12:26.460
and creeped out
that woman at Zales.

12:26.460 --> 12:28.670
This whole day
had no productive outcome.

12:28.670 --> 12:31.290
And I'm gonna get a zero
on my science notebook entry.

12:31.290 --> 12:32.670
Who cares?

12:32.670 --> 12:34.290
I'll write you a note.

12:34.290 --> 12:36.290
You have got to lighten up,
or before you know it,

12:36.290 --> 12:38.790
you're going to be drinking
yak butter in Nepal.

12:38.790 --> 12:40.210
That sounds
like Disneyland

12:40.210 --> 12:41.710
compared to
the Zales experience.

12:44.000 --> 12:47.210
What is Chloe Brown Mueller
doing in our front yard?!

12:48.710 --> 12:50.120
If I let you drive,
would you run her over?

12:50.120 --> 12:51.250
Mom.
Come on.

12:51.250 --> 12:52.380
They'd try you as a kid,

12:52.380 --> 12:53.790
and then you'd be out
in 18 months.

12:53.790 --> 12:55.960
[ Tires screeching ]

12:58.080 --> 12:59.330
[ Sighs ]

12:59.330 --> 13:00.830
[ Vehicle doors close ]

13:00.830 --> 13:05.210
I told you that I don't want
your signs in my yard!

13:05.210 --> 13:07.380
Yeah, that's why I did it
when you weren't home, dum-dum.

13:07.380 --> 13:08.710
Well,
I'm pulling them out!

13:08.710 --> 13:11.000
Go right ahead.
I posted this all on Instagram.

13:11.000 --> 13:12.620
The poors are gonna
drop their Whoppers

13:12.620 --> 13:13.710
and their 40-ounce colas

13:13.710 --> 13:15.920
and vote Chloe Brown Mueller,
baby!

13:15.920 --> 13:17.250
You can't trespass
on my property

13:17.250 --> 13:19.380
and stick your stupid signs
in my lawn!

13:19.380 --> 13:21.290
Oh, speaking of stupid things
stuck in the grass,

13:21.290 --> 13:22.290
nice flamingo.

13:22.290 --> 13:23.540
Ull!
I like it.

13:23.540 --> 13:25.290
It's witty
and unexpected.

13:25.290 --> 13:27.040
It's not witty
and unexpected, Maria!

13:27.040 --> 13:28.250
It's trashy and crappy!

13:28.250 --> 13:29.540
Isn't that
what you meant?

13:29.540 --> 13:32.620
It belonged to my grandmother.
She collected them.

13:32.620 --> 13:35.210
And I like to keep one
in my yard to remind me of her.

13:35.210 --> 13:36.500
Oh, you're killing me!

13:36.500 --> 13:39.290
Your grandmother collected
plastic flamingos?

13:39.290 --> 13:40.670
What else
did she collect?

13:40.670 --> 13:42.120
[ Laughs ]

13:42.120 --> 13:44.040
Quick -- Maria, give me
some trashy and crappy things

13:44.040 --> 13:46.000
so I can ask Katie if
her grandmother collected them.

13:46.000 --> 13:47.500
Um, I...

13:47.500 --> 13:49.210
Oh, my God, you're useless.
Get in the car!

13:49.210 --> 13:50.620
I don't know why I pay
your health insurance.

13:50.620 --> 13:52.250
I have
a $12,000 deductible.

13:52.250 --> 13:54.000
Doesn't mean
you can't fix that chin!

13:54.000 --> 13:56.710
♪♪

14:00.830 --> 14:02.960
Grandma to the rescue!

14:02.960 --> 14:04.250
We are going to flamingo

14:04.250 --> 14:06.080
Chloe Brown Mueller's lawn
tonight.

14:06.080 --> 14:07.250
What does that even mean?

14:07.250 --> 14:10.540
You put flamingos
in someone's yard.

14:10.540 --> 14:11.880
Like, a lot of them.

14:11.880 --> 14:13.250
How is that a good idea?

14:13.250 --> 14:15.210
You said that
before we went into Zales,

14:15.210 --> 14:16.960
and we got
free sparkling waters.

14:16.960 --> 14:20.290
♪♪

14:20.290 --> 14:22.170
So, you have a friend
coming over?

14:22.170 --> 14:23.540
Yeah.
We really hit it off.

14:23.540 --> 14:25.330
Thanks for making me
get back out there.

14:25.330 --> 14:26.540
Ever since Stan left --

14:26.540 --> 14:27.710
Piece of advice --

14:27.710 --> 14:30.000
don't talk about Stan
with this new guy.

14:30.000 --> 14:32.420
He does not want to picture you
with another dad.

14:32.420 --> 14:33.580
Got it.

14:33.580 --> 14:36.210
[ Doorbell rings ]

14:36.210 --> 14:37.830
That must be
your playdate.

14:37.830 --> 14:39.420
Our playdate.
Sure.

14:39.420 --> 14:41.210
I'm not a big fan
of this Cassidy girl,

14:41.210 --> 14:44.080
so let's say
we have a hard out at 5:00.

14:44.080 --> 14:46.210
Okay. Come on.

14:49.000 --> 14:50.500
Greg: Hi.
Hi!

14:50.500 --> 14:51.750
Where's your dad?

14:51.750 --> 14:53.330
He's playing tennis
with his buddies.

14:54.790 --> 14:56.000
Oh, I thought --

14:56.000 --> 14:57.170
Sounds fun.

14:57.170 --> 14:58.250
Come on in.

14:58.250 --> 14:59.500
Yay!

14:59.500 --> 15:01.580
♪♪

15:05.170 --> 15:07.580
New plan -- I'm gonna
play with her for 10 minutes,

15:07.580 --> 15:10.040
and then I'm gonna
make myself throw up.

15:10.040 --> 15:14.710
♪♪

15:14.710 --> 15:16.580
This is going to make
Chloe Brown Mueller

15:16.580 --> 15:17.960
lose her mind.

15:17.960 --> 15:19.540
I would not want
to be Maria tomorrow.

15:19.540 --> 15:20.710
Or ever.

15:20.710 --> 15:22.290
That is one sad lady.

15:22.290 --> 15:23.380
Honestly,
I don't understand why

15:23.380 --> 15:25.670
putting flamingos
in someone's yard is fun.

15:25.670 --> 15:27.880
If you only learn
one thing from me,

15:27.880 --> 15:30.750
it's that nothing is more fun
than messing with people.

15:30.750 --> 15:32.080
Seriously?!

15:32.080 --> 15:34.040
That's the one thing you want me
to learn from my mother?

15:34.040 --> 15:36.670
Well...that and...

15:36.670 --> 15:38.290
compassion, I guess.

15:38.290 --> 15:40.000
You keep up
with the flamingos.

15:40.000 --> 15:41.710
I'm gonna go draw
some more penises.

15:41.710 --> 15:44.210
Ooh! The L's in "Mueller"
are gonna have a sword fight!

15:45.380 --> 15:46.830
[ Siren wailing ]

15:46.830 --> 15:48.120
Cops!

15:48.120 --> 15:49.580
Scatter!
We'll meet at the house!

15:49.580 --> 15:54.080
♪♪

15:54.080 --> 15:55.710
If it makes you feel
any better,

15:55.710 --> 15:57.290
at least your wife didn't
sleep with your best friend,

15:57.290 --> 15:59.120
like McDreamy.

15:59.120 --> 16:01.120
Oh, but then you'd have to have
a best friend first.

16:01.120 --> 16:02.170
Ooh!

16:02.170 --> 16:03.670
Way to go, McDummy.

16:03.670 --> 16:05.460
Guys, your mom
is my best friend.

16:05.460 --> 16:07.250
Problem is,
I can't meet her for drinks

16:07.250 --> 16:08.710
when I'm trying
to get away from her.

16:08.710 --> 16:09.880
[ Breathing heavily ]

16:09.880 --> 16:12.710
Oh, my God!
I got to lay down!

16:12.710 --> 16:15.170
I can't. I can't make it
to the couch.

16:15.170 --> 16:16.790
[ Exhales deeply ]

16:16.790 --> 16:18.170
W-Where's Oliver?

16:18.170 --> 16:19.750
He'll be here
in a second.

16:19.750 --> 16:21.250
He's faster than me,

16:21.250 --> 16:23.330
but I kind of went
as the crow flies.

16:24.670 --> 16:26.250
[ Dog barking ]

16:26.250 --> 16:27.250
[ Grunts ]

16:27.250 --> 16:31.250
♪♪

16:31.250 --> 16:37.250
♪♪

16:41.040 --> 16:42.120
How old are you?

16:42.120 --> 16:43.040
18.

16:43.040 --> 16:44.250
Okay, have at it.

16:44.250 --> 16:46.290
♪♪

16:46.290 --> 16:47.750
What happened?

16:47.750 --> 16:48.920
We had to scatter!

16:48.920 --> 16:50.500
And I'm fat, Greg!

16:50.500 --> 16:53.080
I'm a big girl,
so it was harder for me!

16:53.080 --> 16:54.620
Scatter from what?

16:54.620 --> 16:56.170
[ Cellphone rings ]

16:58.540 --> 17:00.210
Hello?

17:00.210 --> 17:01.580
Yes, this is he.

17:03.120 --> 17:05.040
Oh, I'm...sorry
to hear that, officer.

17:05.040 --> 17:06.170
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:06.170 --> 17:07.830
Yes, we'll be
right down.

17:07.830 --> 17:08.960
[ Exhales sharply ]

17:08.960 --> 17:11.080
Scatter from the cops.

17:11.080 --> 17:14.960
♪♪

17:14.960 --> 17:16.790
I can't believe
you got our son arrested.

17:16.790 --> 17:18.830
You keep saying that
over and over again.

17:18.830 --> 17:20.000
Let's move on.

17:20.000 --> 17:21.170
What was I
supposed to do?

17:21.170 --> 17:22.250
Not get him arrested?

17:22.250 --> 17:23.420
I've been caught
by the cops

17:23.420 --> 17:25.380
for flamingoing lawns
before, Greg.

17:25.380 --> 17:28.080
They give you
a slap on the wrist.

17:28.080 --> 17:30.170
Sometimes,
they ask you out.

17:30.170 --> 17:32.210
Sometimes, you end up
going to the prom

17:32.210 --> 17:33.170
with a police officer.

17:35.290 --> 17:37.920
Trust me --
it's not a big deal.

17:37.920 --> 17:39.790
I hope you're right.

17:39.790 --> 17:41.750
Remember
before we moved here?

17:41.750 --> 17:43.750
Oliver was less serious.

17:43.750 --> 17:45.170
He was goofier.

17:45.170 --> 17:46.620
And then
we come to Westport,

17:46.620 --> 17:48.920
and he has gotten obsessed
with all the wrong things.

17:48.920 --> 17:50.540
And now
he's on that path.

17:50.540 --> 17:52.330
There's a lot of good things
on that path,

17:52.330 --> 17:54.250
like hard work
and a great college.

17:54.250 --> 17:55.620
I don't want him
off the path.

17:55.620 --> 17:58.250
I just want him to have fun
along the way.

17:58.250 --> 18:00.120
And I'm afraid
if he doesn't,

18:00.120 --> 18:03.540
he's gonna end up like Stan
and have a nervous breakdown.

18:03.540 --> 18:07.000
I mean, when was the last time
you heard him laugh?

18:07.000 --> 18:08.210
I miss that.

18:09.500 --> 18:10.460
I miss it, too.

18:13.250 --> 18:14.750
I can't believe
you got our son arrested!

18:14.750 --> 18:16.500
He was
supposed to scatter!

18:16.500 --> 18:22.500
♪♪

18:22.500 --> 18:24.120
We're here to pick up
our son -- Oliver Otto.

18:24.120 --> 18:25.210
Oliver Otto -- right.

18:25.210 --> 18:27.420
We can't release him
to you just yet.

18:27.420 --> 18:28.960
You want to keep him
for, like, an hour or so,

18:28.960 --> 18:31.290
put a scare into him --
is that what you're thinking?

18:31.290 --> 18:32.920
No, your son
is in real trouble.

18:32.920 --> 18:34.620
He was caught
trespassing,

18:34.620 --> 18:36.830
and he caused
substantial property damage.

18:36.830 --> 18:39.460
Mrs. Brown Mueller
is a political candidate,

18:39.460 --> 18:41.830
so there's an extra set
of special circumstances.

18:41.830 --> 18:43.830
It's flamingoing.
In Florida --

18:43.830 --> 18:45.380
This isn't Florida!

18:45.380 --> 18:47.710
Are you familiar with the term
"zero tolerance"?

18:47.710 --> 18:49.250
Because that's
what you're up against.

18:49.250 --> 18:52.040
He drew genitalia
on official election materials.

18:54.250 --> 18:55.670
Can I at least post bail
and bring him home?

18:55.670 --> 18:57.250
Of course --
right after he's arraigned,

18:57.250 --> 18:58.670
which is
in about two days.

18:58.670 --> 19:00.250
Two days?!

19:00.250 --> 19:03.000
You cannot keep a kid in jail
for two days for flamingoing.

19:03.000 --> 19:05.170
This is
a Class "A" misdemeanor.

19:05.170 --> 19:07.290
You'll probably want
to hire an attorney,

19:07.290 --> 19:08.750
because this is
the kind of thing

19:08.750 --> 19:10.540
that goes on
your permanent record.

19:10.540 --> 19:12.920
Oh, my God, Greg!
Permanent record!

19:12.920 --> 19:14.380
This'll prevent him
from going to college!

19:14.380 --> 19:15.500
What are we
going to do?!

19:15.500 --> 19:16.500
Gotcha!

19:16.500 --> 19:17.710
[ Both laugh ]

19:17.710 --> 19:19.380
What?!
I got you!

19:19.380 --> 19:22.580
Special circumstances,
zero tolerance? Classic!

19:22.580 --> 19:24.710
I always giggle
when I'm nervous.

19:24.710 --> 19:25.710
I almost giggled.

19:25.710 --> 19:27.170
You should have seen
your face, Mom.

19:27.170 --> 19:28.420
You were totally
freaked out.

19:28.420 --> 19:30.880
Why in the world
would you do that?

19:30.880 --> 19:33.750
Because nothing is more fun
than messing with people.

19:33.750 --> 19:36.120
♪♪

19:36.120 --> 19:37.210
[ Chuckles ]

19:38.460 --> 19:40.460
You really are
a good student.

19:40.460 --> 19:42.420
You were, like,
"Oh, my God, Greg!

19:42.420 --> 19:43.710
Permanent record"!

19:43.710 --> 19:46.000
[ Laughing ]

19:46.000 --> 19:47.460
Well,
you found his laugh.

19:47.460 --> 19:48.750
Yeah.

19:48.750 --> 19:50.500
I didn't miss it
as much as I thought I did.

19:50.500 --> 19:51.540
[ Laughing continues ]

19:56.040 --> 19:57.420
So,
when I get arrested,

19:57.420 --> 19:58.960
are you going to throw
a dinner in my honor?

19:58.960 --> 20:01.210
I don't like
how she said "when".

20:01.210 --> 20:03.170
You should know that
I've decided to quit Mandarin.

20:03.170 --> 20:04.250
Are you sure?

20:04.250 --> 20:06.120
Yeah, I'm gonna
take Latin instead.

20:06.120 --> 20:07.880
It's a dead language.

20:07.880 --> 20:10.500
Jeremy Fleisher's parents
can do a lot of things,

20:10.500 --> 20:12.540
but they can't buy him
a dead person.

20:12.540 --> 20:13.880
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:18.670 --> 20:20.460
Hi! Come on in.
How are you?

20:20.460 --> 20:22.540
Oh, my God -- cops.
Oliver, run!

20:22.540 --> 20:23.580
No, Anna-Kat,
it's okay.

20:23.580 --> 20:24.830
We got to talking
in the station.

20:24.830 --> 20:26.380
I found out we have
a lot of the same interests.

20:26.380 --> 20:27.540
You made a friend?

20:27.540 --> 20:29.380
That's right.
We're both philatelists.

20:29.380 --> 20:32.380
Greg is one of the most
passionate philatelists

20:32.380 --> 20:33.380
I've ever met.

20:33.380 --> 20:34.460
[ Chuckling ] Oh!

20:34.460 --> 20:36.290
I know it means
something different

20:36.290 --> 20:38.250
than what
I'm thinking it means.

20:38.250 --> 20:39.420
It means
"stamp collecting".

20:39.420 --> 20:41.290
There it is.

20:41.290 --> 20:42.420
♪♪
